@startuml atomics
title Atomic primitives — MEM_ADD / MEM_CAS (feature 0x02)
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Node A" as A
participant "Coordinator\n(serializes every request)" as C
participant "Node B" as B

== MEM_ADD: read-modify-write in one round-trip ==

note over C : counter at ""ref"" is 42

A -> C : MEM_ADD [ref u32][delta = +1]
note over C : *ref += 1 happens **inside** the\ncoordinator's serialization window\n— no lock, no lease, race-free
C --> A : MEM_DATA [old = 42]

B -> C : MEM_ADD [ref][+1]
C --> B : MEM_DATA [old = 43]
note right of B
  One round-trip replaces
  LOCK / READ / WRITE / UNLOCK —
  measured 1.5 s vs 10.2 s (queued
  locks) for 150 contended
  increments on the 6-node swarm.
end note

== MEM_CAS: optimistic update, the old value says who won ==

note over C : value at ""ref"" is 44

A -> C : MEM_CAS [ref][expected = 44][desired = 100]
C --> A : MEM_DATA [old = 44]
note right of A : old == expected → **won**;\n44 → 100 was written

B -> C : MEM_CAS [ref][expected = 44][desired = 200]
C --> B : MEM_DATA [old = 100]
note right of B : old ≠ expected → **lost**, memory\nuntouched; re-read, recompute,\nCAS again

== Both respect explicit locks ==

B -> C : LOCK [region]
C --> B : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]
A -> C : MEM_ADD [ref in that region][+1]
C --> A : ERROR [LOCKED]
note right of A : module sees WASP_REMOTE_ELOCKED —\natomics compose with lock-based code
@enduml
